          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used from private or public recitation, prayer, and observance during the month of Bhādra (August/September) of rites employed to ward off problems (aduḥkha), such as evil and sin, for the coming year. It includes a section called the Pūjāvidhi, on worshiping the goddess Parvātī, as well as a section on mythology related to the observance.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Aduḥkhanavamīkathā</title>
              <title type="vernacular">अदुःखनवमीकथा</title>
